			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p35306">Which Roomba for cat hair?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=35306&amp;sid=028e370868ce9d2b00f09889c94ad56b#p35306"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5406&amp;sid=028e370868ce9d2b00f09889c94ad56b">sunbeltsue</a></strong> &raquo; October 1st, 2007, 1:22 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">Currently I own/love Dirt Dog (April 2007) and the blue/grey Roomba Scheduler (March 2007).   
<br />
<br />I want to give my adult children--both of whom have cats--a Roomba for Christmas.  Since the Roomba for pets is discontinued, which Roomba below is a better value and /or easier on my wallet:
<br />
<br />o The new 535 reviewed by MadScientist on Sept 25?  I think I saw it online for around $213 or $249.
<br />or
<br />o The Blue/greay Roomba Scheduler being closed out for $180?
<br />
<br />
<br />o</div>

			

		</div>

		
